            "v": "I see, Lord! I see! I am in the temple, facing outward toward the entrance. The doors are opening and the brilliance of Your glory is flooding the room. Before me is the altar, and upon it I see a white napkin. It is being folded without hands. There is water being poured out of the air just above it. The water is beautiful and sparkling. It is being poured upon the napkin, but doesn’t seem to be reaching it... Lord, I am thirsty. May I drink from this fountain?"
