          {
            "t": "text",
            "v": "From it shall you drink. Place it flat in your hand, and bring it to your lips when you thirst. Inhale deeply through your nose, then place the napkin between your lips and drink. Drink deeply, My son, for it is time. Now place it within the pocket of your robe and take it with you, that you may also wring it out on the thirsty; share it with all you meet. For the dampness thereof shall never run dry, no matter the number of times you use it; nor will it wear thin, nor tear, nor can its surface be blemished."
          }
